SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 428
By Watson
A RESOLUTION to recognize and congratulate Chattanooga
Employees Federal Credit Union on the
occasion of its 100th anniversary.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly recognize those
dynamic financial institutions whose contributions have been vital to the economic life of their
respective communities; and
WHEREAS, for the past century, Chattanooga Federal Employees Credit Union has
capably served and earned the trust of customers in Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, a not-for-profit, member-owned financial institution that exists to serve its
members, Chattanooga Federal was chartered on January 13, 1925, and is the oldest
established credit union in the region; and
WHEREAS, Chattanooga Federal offers a complete line of financial products and
services to meet customer needs; and
WHEREAS, all family members of those eligible for membership may also join the credit
union and take advantage of the many services; and
WHEREAS, by virtue of being a member of Chattanooga Federal, individuals' savings
are federally insured to at least $250,000 and backed by the full faith and credit of the United
States Government through the National Credit Union Administration, a U.S. Government
agency; and
WHEREAS, Chattanooga Federal has demonstrated a steadfast commitment to
excellence for a century now, serving customers with nothing less than the utmost
professionalism and financial acumen; now, therefore,
